1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:03,671
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

2
00:00:07,800 --> 00:00:09,885
NOVAKOVICH:
HOW CAN YOU EAT THAT STUFF?

3
00:00:09,927 --> 00:00:11,470
CUTLER:
IT'S HEALTHIER THAN THAT.

4
00:00:11,512 --> 00:00:13,639
NOVAKOVICH: HUH. AT LEAST
THIS TASTES LIKE SOMETHING.

5
00:00:13,681 --> 00:00:16,475
CUTLER: I GUESS IT JUST TAKES
A MORE DISCRIMINATING PALATE

6
00:00:16,517 --> 00:00:17,977
TO APPRECIATE VULCAN CUISINE.

7
00:00:18,018 --> 00:00:19,728
NOVAKOVICH: [ LAUGHING ]

8
00:00:19,770 --> 00:00:23,022
CUTLER: DID YOU KNOW THERE WERE
OVER 5,000 SUBSPECIES OF TERMITE

9
00:00:23,064 --> 00:00:24,441
ON LORACUS PRIME?

10
00:00:24,483 --> 00:00:25,442
NOVAKOVICH: HMM.

11
00:00:25,484 --> 00:00:27,528
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

12
00:00:35,661 --> 00:00:39,581
NOVAKOVICH: I THOUGHT WE WERE
HEADED FOR A NEBULA.

13
00:00:39,623 --> 00:00:41,876
CUTLER:
ANYBODY HEAR ABOUT THIS?

14
00:00:41,917 --> 00:00:43,168
MAN: NOT A WORD.

15
00:00:43,210 --> 00:00:46,005
CUTLER: I WONDER IF SOMEBODY
LIVES THERE.

16
00:00:46,045 --> 00:00:47,172
NOVAKOVICH:
THERE'S A LOT OF PLANT LIFE.

17
00:00:47,214 --> 00:00:48,716
IT MIGHT BE AN OXYGEN
ATMOSPHERE.

18
00:00:48,757 --> 00:00:52,302
CUTLER: HMM. WHAT DO YOU THINK?
FIRST CONTACT?

19
00:00:52,344 --> 00:00:54,304
MAN: I DON'T SEE ANY CITIES
OR AGRICULTURE.

20
00:00:54,346 --> 00:00:57,182
NOVAKOVICH: MAYBE THEY LIVE
UNDERGROUND OR IN THE WATER.

21
00:00:57,224 --> 00:00:59,852
CUTLER: IS THAT SNOW
ON THOSE MOUNTAINS?

22
00:00:59,894 --> 00:01:01,436
NOVAKOVICH: YOU'D THINK
THE CAPTAIN WOULD MAKE

23
00:01:01,478 --> 00:01:03,271
AN ANNOUNCEMENT OR SOMETHING.

24
00:01:03,313 --> 00:01:05,983
CUTLER: WELL, CALL HIM.

25
00:01:06,025 --> 00:01:07,401
ARCHER: T'POL?

26
00:01:07,442 --> 00:01:11,112
T'POL: 17% OXYGEN, 81% NITROGEN.

27
00:01:11,154 --> 00:01:12,948
TUCKER:
SOUNDS LIKE HOME.

28
00:01:12,990 --> 00:01:13,991
ARCHER: ANY PEOPLE?

29
00:01:14,033 --> 00:01:15,868
T'POL: THE PLANET SUPPORTS

30
00:01:15,910 --> 00:01:18,996
A DIVERSE ECOLOGY, BUT THERE
ARE NO SIGNS OF HUMANOID LIFE.

31
00:01:19,038 --> 00:01:23,208
ARCHER: STILL, SOMEONE
MAY HAVE A CLAIM ON IT.

32
00:01:23,250 --> 00:01:25,252
WE DON'T WANT TO GO WALTZING
INTO THEIR BACK YARD.

33
00:01:25,293 --> 00:01:31,299
SCAN FOR MARKER BUOYS, BEACONS,
MANMADE SATELLITES.

34
00:01:31,341 --> 00:01:32,676
REED: NONE IN RANGE, SIR.

35
00:01:32,718 --> 00:01:35,679
LOOKS LIKE NO ONE'S
PLANTED A FLAG JUST YET.

36
00:01:37,222 --> 00:01:40,642
ARCHER:
PREP A SHUTTLEPOD, MR. TUCKER.

37
00:01:40,684 --> 00:01:43,604
I LIKE THE LOOKS
OF THE NORTHERN CONTINENT.

38
00:01:43,645 --> 00:01:45,940
SEE IF YOU CAN FIND
A GOOD PLACE TO SET DOWN.

39
00:01:45,981 --> 00:01:47,106
MAYWEATHER: YES, SIR.

40
00:01:47,148 --> 00:01:48,734
T'POL: CAPTAIN,

41
00:01:48,776 --> 00:01:52,320
THERE ARE A NUMBER OF PROTOCOLS
YOU MAY WANT TO CONSIDER.

42
00:01:52,362 --> 00:01:54,073
ARCHER: PROTOCOLS.

43
00:01:54,114 --> 00:01:56,033
T'POL: VULCAN SHIPS WOULD BEGIN
BY SENDING AUTOMATED PROBES DOWN

44
00:01:56,075 --> 00:01:58,285
TO COLLECT MORE DETAILED SCANS.

45
00:01:58,326 --> 00:02:00,996
IF THE PLANET PROVED
TO BE MINSHARA-CLASS,

46
00:02:01,038 --> 00:02:04,124
WE WOULD THEN CONDUCT A
GEOPHYSICAL SURVEY FROM ORBIT.

47
00:02:04,165 --> 00:02:05,667
MAYWEATHER: MINSHARA-CLASS?

48
00:02:05,709 --> 00:02:08,295
SATO: SUITABLE
FOR HUMANOID LIFE.

49
00:02:08,336 --> 00:02:10,547
ARCHER:
HOW LONG WOULD ALL THAT TAKE?

50
00:02:10,589 --> 00:02:12,633
T'POL: SIX OR SEVEN DAYS.

51
00:02:12,674 --> 00:02:14,969
TUCKER: YOU EXPECT US
TO SIT UP HERE FOR A WEEK

52
00:02:15,010 --> 00:02:18,138
WHILE PROBES HAVE ALL THE FUN?

53
00:02:18,179 --> 00:02:20,390
T'POL: THIS PLANET HAS BEEN HERE
A LONG TIME.

54
00:02:20,432 --> 00:02:23,310
IT WILL STILL BE HERE
IN SEVEN DAYS.

55
00:02:23,351 --> 00:02:27,648
ARCHER: I UNDERSTAND THAT YOU
HAVE A MORE CAUTIOUS APPROACH,

56
00:02:27,689 --> 00:02:31,110
BUT WE DIDN'T COME OUT HERE
TO TIPTOE AROUND.

57
00:02:31,151 --> 00:02:32,736
GET THE POD READY.

58
00:02:32,778 --> 00:02:37,282
I'D LIKE YOU TO PUT TOGETHER
THE SURVEY TEAM.

59
00:02:37,324 --> 00:02:40,285
I ASSUME THAT'S NOT A VIOLATION
OF PROTOCOL.

60
00:02:43,831 --> 00:02:48,460
RUSSELL WATSON:
♪ IT'S BEEN A LONG ROAD ♪

61
00:02:48,502 --> 00:02:51,713
♪ GETTING FROM THERE TO HERE ♪

62
00:02:51,755 --> 00:02:55,550
♪ IT'S BEEN A LONG TIME ♪

63
00:02:55,592 --> 00:02:59,262
♪ BUT MY TIME IS FINALLY NEAR ♪

64
00:02:59,304 --> 00:03:03,642
♪ AND I WILL SEE MY DREAM
COME ALIVE AT LAST ♪

65
00:03:03,684 --> 00:03:07,228
♪ I WILL TOUCH THE SKY ♪

66
00:03:07,270 --> 00:03:11,232
♪ AND THEY'RE NOT GONNA
HOLD ME DOWN NO MORE ♪

67
00:03:11,274 --> 00:03:14,235
♪ NO, THEY'RE
NOT GONNA CHANGE MY MIND ♪

68
00:03:14,277 --> 00:03:17,447
♪ 'CAUSE I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

69
00:03:17,489 --> 00:03:19,116
♪ OF THE HEART ♪

70
00:03:19,158 --> 00:03:22,786
♪ I'M GOING WHERE MY HEART
WILL TAKE ME ♪

71
00:03:22,828 --> 00:03:27,541
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH TO BELIEVE ♪

72
00:03:27,582 --> 00:03:29,960
♪ I CAN DO ANYTHING ♪

73
00:03:30,002 --> 00:03:34,840
♪ I'VE GOT STRENGTH
OF THE SOUL ♪

74
00:03:34,882 --> 00:03:37,634
♪ AND NO ONE'S GONNA BEND
OR BREAK ME ♪

75
00:03:37,676 --> 00:03:43,306
♪ I CAN REACH ANY STAR ♪

76
00:03:43,348 --> 00:03:45,225
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

77
00:03:45,266 --> 00:03:47,644
♪ I'VE GOT, I'VE GOT, I'VE GOT ♪

78
00:03:47,686 --> 00:03:50,981
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

79
00:03:51,023 --> 00:03:56,028
♪ FAITH OF THE HEART ♪

80
00:04:11,168 --> 00:04:12,753
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

81
00:04:16,297 --> 00:04:18,133
MAN: THANKS.

82
00:04:20,343 --> 00:04:22,303
CUTLER: I TRIED SOME PLOMEEK
BROTH THIS MORNING.

83
00:04:22,345 --> 00:04:26,934
IT WAS VERY GOOD.
VULCAN FOOD IS...INTERESTING.

84
00:04:26,975 --> 00:04:29,269
T'POL: DID YOU STERILIZE
THE SAMPLE CONTAINERS?

85
00:04:29,310 --> 00:04:31,063
CUTLER: YES.

86
00:04:35,776 --> 00:04:38,153
THANKS FOR CHOOSING ME
FOR THIS MISSION.

87
00:04:38,195 --> 00:04:41,406
T'POL: YOU WERE SELECTED BECAUSE
YOUR SPECIALTY IS ENTOMOLOGY.

88
00:04:41,448 --> 00:04:45,786
THIS PLANET HAS
A DIVERSE INSECT POPULATION.

89
00:04:45,827 --> 00:04:48,247
CUTLER: RIGHT.

90
00:04:50,624 --> 00:04:54,169
TUCKER: YOU'D HAVE BETTER LUCK
MAKING FRIENDS WITH A HOUSEFLY.

91
00:04:54,211 --> 00:04:55,879
CUTLER: YEAH.

92
00:05:11,853 --> 00:05:13,354
TUCKER: WOW.

93
00:05:13,396 --> 00:05:15,356
CUTLER:
WORTH EVERY LIGHT-YEAR.

94
00:05:15,398 --> 00:05:18,152
ARCHER: SET US DOWN JUST EAST
OF THOSE HILLS.

95
00:05:18,193 --> 00:05:19,611
MAYWEATHER: AYE, SIR.

96
00:05:28,453 --> 00:05:30,080
PORTHOS: [ BARKS ]

97
00:05:37,462 --> 00:05:40,007
TUCKER:
WHERE NO DOG HAS GONE BEFORE.

98
00:05:40,048 --> 00:05:41,382
ARCHER: [ LAUGHS ]

99
00:05:41,424 --> 00:05:43,844
OH, I ALMOST FORGOT
WHAT FRESH AIR SMELLS LIKE.

100
00:05:43,885 --> 00:05:45,971
T'POL: THE ATMOSPHERE
CONTAINS TRACE ELEMENTS

101
00:05:46,013 --> 00:05:48,182
OF NITROGEN DIOXIDE,
CHLOROMETHANE --

102
00:05:48,223 --> 00:05:49,850
ARCHER:
PUT THAT THING AWAY.

103
00:05:49,891 --> 00:05:53,645
TAKE A MINUTE TO ENJOY YOURSELF.

104
00:05:53,687 --> 00:05:57,065
THE SKY EVER GET
THIS BLUE ON VULCAN?

105
00:05:57,107 --> 00:05:59,609
T'POL: OCCASIONALLY.

106
00:05:59,651 --> 00:06:01,111
ARCHER: WE'RE WALKING
ON AN ALIEN WORLD,

107
00:06:01,153 --> 00:06:02,737
LIGHT-YEARS FROM EARTH
OR VULCAN.

108
00:06:02,779 --> 00:06:04,281
DOESN'T THAT IMPRESS YOU?

109
00:06:04,323 --> 00:06:06,574
T'POL: I'VE BEEN TO 36
MINSHARA-CLASS PLANETS.

110
00:06:06,616 --> 00:06:10,204
THIS EXPERIENCE IS ONLY
MARGINALLY DIFFERENT.

111
00:06:10,245 --> 00:06:13,207
TUCKER: PERFECT.
HOLD IT RIGHT THERE.

112
00:06:15,292 --> 00:06:17,544
ARCHER: SMILE.

113
00:06:17,585 --> 00:06:19,213
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

114
00:06:19,254 --> 00:06:22,590
BE SURE TO GET A COPY OF THAT
TO THE VULCAN HIGH COMMAND.

115
00:06:23,675 --> 00:06:25,552
T'POL: YOU HAVE
YOUR ASSIGNMENTS.

116
00:06:25,593 --> 00:06:27,929
WE'LL RENDEZVOUS
HERE AT 1900 HOURS...

117
00:06:27,971 --> 00:06:31,725
UNLESS THE CAPTAIN WANTS US
TO POSE FOR MORE PICTURES.

118
00:06:58,459 --> 00:07:00,379
[ SNIFFS ]

119
00:07:06,051 --> 00:07:09,596
ARCHER: I'M AFRAID MY LOG ENTRY
ISN'T GONNA DO THIS JUSTICE.

120
00:07:09,637 --> 00:07:12,266
TUCKER: A CABIN IN THESE WOODS
WOULD BE NICE.

121
00:07:12,307 --> 00:07:13,892
ARCHER: THREE WEEKS
IN DEEP SPACE,

122
00:07:13,934 --> 00:07:15,560
YOU'RE READY TO JUMP SHIP?

123
00:07:15,602 --> 00:07:18,479
TUCKER: [ LAUGHS ] DON'T WORRY.
I'M NOT GOING ANYWHERE.

124
00:07:18,521 --> 00:07:19,647
YOU GUYS'D BE LOST WITHOUT ME.

125
00:07:19,689 --> 00:07:21,233
[ CHUCKLES ]

126
00:07:21,275 --> 00:07:22,401
MAYWEATHER: IT'S BEAUTIFUL,
ALL RIGHT,

127
00:07:22,442 --> 00:07:23,735
BUT I COULDN'T CALL A PLACE HOME

128
00:07:23,777 --> 00:07:25,320
UNLESS IT CAME WITH A PAIR
OF WARP NACELLES.

129
00:07:25,362 --> 00:07:27,155
TUCKER: BOOMERS.

130
00:07:27,197 --> 00:07:30,033
[ COMMUNICATOR BEEPS ]

131
00:07:30,075 --> 00:07:31,492
ARCHER: ARCHER.

132
00:07:31,534 --> 00:07:33,661
T'POL: IS THERE
A PROBLEM, CAPTAIN?

133
00:07:33,703 --> 00:07:35,330
ARCHER: NO, NO PROBLEM. WHY?

134
00:07:35,372 --> 00:07:39,084
T'POL: WE WERE SCHEDULED TO
RENDEZVOUS 15 MINUTES AGO.

135
00:07:41,711 --> 00:07:45,882
ARCHER: SORRY.
WE LOST TRACK OF TIME.

136
00:07:45,924 --> 00:07:47,968
WE'LL BE RIGHT THERE.

137
00:07:54,182 --> 00:07:57,227
T'POL: WE'VE IDENTIFIED SEVERAL
NOCTURNAL MARSUPIALS.

138
00:07:57,269 --> 00:07:59,479
I'D LIKE TO KEEP CREWMEN
CUTLER AND NOVAKOVICH

139
00:07:59,520 --> 00:08:01,356
WITH ME OVERNIGHT
TO STUDY THEM.

140
00:08:01,398 --> 00:08:02,607
ARCHER: I'M GLAD TO SEE

141
00:08:02,649 --> 00:08:04,609
YOU'RE GETTING
IN THE SPIRIT OF THINGS.

142
00:08:04,651 --> 00:08:05,986
PICK YOU UP IN THE MORNING.

143
00:08:06,027 --> 00:08:07,321
TUCKER: CAPTAIN, IF IT'S
ALL RIGHT WITH YOU,

144
00:08:07,362 --> 00:08:09,530
TRAVIS AND I WOULD LIKE
TO STAY AS WELL.

145
00:08:09,572 --> 00:08:11,158
MAYWEATHER: WE WOULD?

146
00:08:11,199 --> 00:08:12,909
TUCKER: WHEN'S THE LAST TIME
YOU SLEPT UNDER THE STARS?

147
00:08:12,951 --> 00:08:14,995
THERE'S PLENTY OF CAMPING GEAR
IN THE POD.

148
00:08:15,036 --> 00:08:17,831
T'POL: THIS ISN'T SHORE LEAVE.
THIS IS A RESEARCH MISSION.

149
00:08:17,872 --> 00:08:20,417
ARCHER: WHY CAN'T IT BE
A LITTLE BIT OF BOTH?

150
00:08:20,459 --> 00:08:24,545
RESEARCH ISN'T THE ONLY REASON
WE'RE OUT HERE.

151
00:08:24,587 --> 00:08:26,840
PITCH YOUR TENT, COMMANDER.

152
00:08:26,881 --> 00:08:28,258
TUCKER:
THANKS, CAPTAIN.

153
00:08:28,300 --> 00:08:31,052
DON'T WORRY.
WE'LL KEEP OUT OF YOUR HAIR.

154
00:08:34,555 --> 00:08:37,309
MAYWEATHER: KEEP IN MIND
THOSE CARGO VESSELS

155
00:08:37,351 --> 00:08:39,769
WEREN'T EQUIPPED
FOR RESCUE OPERATIONS.

156
00:08:39,811 --> 00:08:41,938
SO THE CAPTAIN WASN'T
SURE WHAT TO DO

157
00:08:41,980 --> 00:08:44,691
WHEN HE PICKED UP
THE DISTRESS CALL.

158
00:08:44,732 --> 00:08:48,736
BUT IT WASN'T A SHIP
THAT SENT THE SIGNAL.

159
00:08:48,778 --> 00:08:50,113
IT WAS A LIFE POD

160
00:08:50,155 --> 00:08:53,950
FROM ONE OF THE OLD
Y-500-CLASS FREIGHTERS.

161
00:08:53,992 --> 00:08:55,576
TUCKER:
THOSE WERE RETIRED DECADES AGO.

162
00:08:55,618 --> 00:08:56,995
MAYWEATHER: EXACTLY.

163
00:08:57,037 --> 00:09:02,876
THE POD HAD BEEN DRIFTING
IN SPACE FOR 63 YEARS.

164
00:09:02,917 --> 00:09:06,587
BIO-SCANS SHOWED ONE LIFE SIGN
INSIDE THE POD...

165
00:09:06,629 --> 00:09:09,466
HUMAN.

166
00:09:09,508 --> 00:09:10,675
THE ASSISTANT ENGINEER,

167
00:09:10,717 --> 00:09:12,677
GEORGE WEBB, A FRIEND
OF MY UNCLE'S,

168
00:09:12,719 --> 00:09:16,264
WAS ASSIGNED TO OPEN IT.

169
00:09:16,306 --> 00:09:20,143
IT TOOK HIM OVER AN HOUR
TO CUT THROUGH THE HULL.

170
00:09:20,185 --> 00:09:26,525
HE SAID THE METAL FELT STRANGE,
COLD TO THE TOUCH.

171
00:09:26,566 --> 00:09:28,026
OF COURSE IT WAS COLD.

172
00:09:28,068 --> 00:09:30,070
TUCKER: IT WAS FLOATING
IN SPACE FOR 60 YEARS.

173
00:09:30,111 --> 00:09:32,906
MAYWEATHER: HE COULD
HEAR A TAPPING NOISE

174
00:09:32,947 --> 00:09:34,908
COMING FROM INSIDE,

175
00:09:34,949 --> 00:09:40,580
BUT WHEN HE FINALLY GOT IT OPEN,
THE POD WAS EMPTY.

176
00:09:40,621 --> 00:09:42,582
NO BODY, NOTHING.

177
00:09:42,623 --> 00:09:46,211
A FEW DAYS LATER,
WEBB STARTED ACTING STRANGE --

178
00:09:46,253 --> 00:09:48,588
GETTING INTO FIGHTS
WITH THE CREW,

179
00:09:48,629 --> 00:09:52,592
MUTTERING TO HIMSELF
IN SOME SORT OF ALIEN LANGUAGE.

180
00:09:52,633 --> 00:09:56,346
THEN ONE DAY, HE LOCKED HIMSELF
IN ENGINEERING

181
00:09:56,388 --> 00:09:58,765
AND OVERLOADED
THE IMPULSE REACTORS.

182
00:09:58,806 --> 00:10:02,602
HE ALMOST DESTROYED THE SHIP.

183
00:10:02,643 --> 00:10:07,065
THEN HE SEALED HIMSELF
IN A LIFE POD AND EJECTED IT.

184
00:10:07,107 --> 00:10:10,110
CUTLER: I ASSUME THE CAPTAIN
WENT AFTER HIM.

185
00:10:10,151 --> 00:10:12,904
MAYWEATHER: THE REACTORS
WERE TOO BADLY DAMAGED.

186
00:10:12,946 --> 00:10:15,740
SOME PEOPLE SAY

187
00:10:15,782 --> 00:10:18,535
IT WAS AN ALIEN LIFE-FORM
THAT GOT INTO HIM.

188
00:10:18,577 --> 00:10:22,038
OTHERS THINK IT WAS
THE GHOST OF A DEAD CREWMAN.

189
00:10:22,080 --> 00:10:25,833
I NEVER KNEW WHAT TO BELIEVE.

190
00:10:25,875 --> 00:10:30,046
BUT WEBB IS STILL OUT THERE,
DRIFTING.

191
00:10:30,088 --> 00:10:33,841
WHEN THE SUBSPACE NOISE
IS REAL LOW,

192
00:10:33,883 --> 00:10:35,302
SOME COM OFFICERS SAY

193
00:10:35,343 --> 00:10:38,679
THEY CAN STILL HEAR THE ECHO
OF HIS DISTRESS CALL.

194
00:10:38,721 --> 00:10:41,015
BEEP.

195
00:10:42,476 --> 00:10:45,270
BEEP.

196
00:10:45,312 --> 00:10:47,939
TUCKER: OOH.

197
00:10:47,981 --> 00:10:49,899
[ LAUGHTER ]

198
00:10:49,941 --> 00:10:52,360
T'POL: IT'S HIGHLY DOUBTFUL
THAT A DISTRESS BEACON

199
00:10:52,402 --> 00:10:56,697
COULD FUNCTION CONTINUOUSLY
FOR 63 YEARS.

200
00:10:56,739 --> 00:10:58,074
TUCKER: [ CHUCKLING ]

201
00:10:58,116 --> 00:11:00,701
LET ME GUESS.

202
00:11:00,743 --> 00:11:03,663
NO GHOST STORIES ON VULCAN.

203
00:11:03,704 --> 00:11:05,582
CUTLER: THAT'S IT.

204
00:11:06,707 --> 00:11:09,586
TO THE LEFT OF
THAT TRINARY CLUSTER.

205
00:11:09,628 --> 00:11:10,587
TUCKER: WHAT?

206
00:11:10,629 --> 00:11:11,588
CUTLER: OUR SUN.

207
00:11:11,630 --> 00:11:12,631
MAYWEATHER: ARE YOU SURE?

208
00:11:12,671 --> 00:11:15,258
CUTLER: YEAH, POSITIVE.

209
00:11:15,300 --> 00:11:18,761
JUST ANOTHER SPECK OF LIGHT,

210
00:11:18,803 --> 00:11:21,640
NO DIFFERENT THAN ANY OTHER.

211
00:11:21,680 --> 00:11:25,268
TUCKER: WHEN I WAS A KID,
I'D GO CAMPING WITH MY BUDDIES.

212
00:11:25,310 --> 00:11:27,604
WE'D SPEND HALF THE NIGHT
LOOKING UP AT THE STARS,

213
00:11:27,646 --> 00:11:32,609
WONDERING WHAT OUR OWN SUN WOULD
LOOK LIKE FROM THIS FAR AWAY.

214
00:11:32,651 --> 00:11:34,902
MAYWEATHER: NOW YOU KNOW.

215
00:11:34,944 --> 00:11:36,946
NOVAKOVICH: [ GROANS ]

216
00:11:36,988 --> 00:11:38,739
CUTLER: ARE YOU OKAY?

217
00:11:38,781 --> 00:11:39,907
NOVAKOVICH: HEADACHE.

218
00:11:39,949 --> 00:11:41,117
IF IT'S ALL RIGHT WITH YOU,

219
00:11:41,159 --> 00:11:42,994
I'D LIKE TO LIE DOWN
FOR A WHILE

220
00:11:43,036 --> 00:11:44,703
BEFORE WE GET BACK TO WORK?

221
00:11:44,745 --> 00:11:46,122
T'POL: CERTAINLY.

222
00:11:51,461 --> 00:11:53,754
TUCKER: HAS ANYONE HEARD THE ONE
ABOUT THE HAUNTED COMET?

223
00:11:53,796 --> 00:11:56,132
[ LAUGHTER ]

224
00:11:56,174 --> 00:11:58,134
CUTLER: WAIT A MINUTE.
YOU NOTICE SOMETHING?

225
00:11:58,176 --> 00:12:00,679
THE FIREFLIES ARE GONE.

226
00:12:00,719 --> 00:12:02,096
TUCKER: NICE GOING, TRAVIS.

227
00:12:02,138 --> 00:12:03,764
YOU SCARED OFF THE BUGS.

228
00:12:03,806 --> 00:12:05,183
MAYWEATHER: [ LAUGHING ]

229
00:12:05,225 --> 00:12:08,019
CUTLER: MAYBE IT'S THE GHOST
OF GEORGE WEBB.

230
00:12:08,061 --> 00:12:11,105
[ WIND GUSTING ]

231
00:12:11,147 --> 00:12:12,982
TUCKER: LOOKS LIKE WE MIGHT HAVE
OURSELVES A LITTLE WEATHER!

232
00:12:13,024 --> 00:12:16,486
T'POL: A FRONT IS APPROACHING
FROM THE SOUTHWEST.

233
00:12:20,739 --> 00:12:23,618
[ THUNDER CRASHING ]

234
00:12:24,869 --> 00:12:27,414
MAYWEATHER:
IT MUST BE GUSTING AT 80 KPH.

235
00:12:27,455 --> 00:12:29,416
TUCKER: THAT'S NOTHING
COMPARED TO A HURRICANE

236
00:12:29,457 --> 00:12:31,000
COMING UP THROUGH
THE FLORIDA KEYS.

237
00:12:31,042 --> 00:12:35,129
MAYWEATHER: TRY FLYING THROUGH
AN ION STORM AT WARP 2.

238
00:12:35,171 --> 00:12:37,840
NOVAKOVICH:
DID YOU HEAR THAT?

239
00:12:37,882 --> 00:12:39,050
CUTLER: WHAT?

240
00:12:39,092 --> 00:12:41,010
NOVAKOVICH:
SOMEONE'S OUT THERE.

241
00:12:41,052 --> 00:12:44,097
CUTLER: IT'S THE WIND.

242
00:12:55,858 --> 00:12:57,068
TUCKER: AAH! SON OF A BITCH!

243
00:12:57,110 --> 00:12:58,236
MAYWEATHER: WHAT IS IT?

244
00:12:58,278 --> 00:13:00,614
TUCKER:
THERE'S SOMETHING IN MY BAG!

245
00:13:00,655 --> 00:13:02,616
GIVE ME YOUR BOOT!

246
00:13:02,657 --> 00:13:03,617
MAYWEATHER: WHAT FOR?

247
00:13:03,658 --> 00:13:05,118
TUCKER: SO I CAN SQUASH IT!

248
00:13:05,159 --> 00:13:06,494
MAYWEATHER: ARE WE ALLOWED
TO SQUASH ALIEN LIFE-FORMS?

249
00:13:06,536 --> 00:13:08,204
TUCKER: IF THEY'RE INSIDE
YOUR SLEEPING BAG!

250
00:13:08,246 --> 00:13:09,830
MAYWEATHER: BUT IT'S NOT INSIDE
THE SLEEPING BAG ANYMORE!

251
00:13:09,872 --> 00:13:12,459
TUCKER: THERE IT IS!
WAIT A MINUTE.

252
00:13:12,500 --> 00:13:13,792
WHERE'D YOU PUT
THE PHASE PISTOLS?

253
00:13:13,834 --> 00:13:15,002
MAYWEATHER:
YOU WANT TO SHOOT A BUG?

254
00:13:15,044 --> 00:13:16,379
TUCKER: I'M JUST GONNA STUN IT.

255
00:13:16,421 --> 00:13:19,299
T'POL: T'POL TO TUCKER.
TUCKER: GO AHEAD.

256
00:13:19,340 --> 00:13:21,384
T'POL: IS THERE
A PROBLEM, COMMANDER?

257
00:13:21,426 --> 00:13:22,801
TUCKER: OH, NO,

258
00:13:22,843 --> 00:13:24,763
JUST AN EIGHT-INCH SCORPION
THING INSIDE OUR TENT.

259
00:13:24,803 --> 00:13:26,931
T'POL: DO YOU REQUIRE
ASSISTANCE?

260
00:13:26,973 --> 00:13:28,600
TUCKER: I THINK I'VE GOT IT
UNDER CONTROL.

261
00:13:28,642 --> 00:13:30,685
NO, NOT THERE, IT'S OVER THERE!

262
00:13:33,354 --> 00:13:36,149
T'POL, YOU SAID YOU FOUND
A CAVE THIS AFTERNOON?

263
00:13:36,190 --> 00:13:38,985
T'POL: LESS THAN HALF
A KILOMETER FROM HERE.

264
00:13:39,026 --> 00:13:40,945
TUCKER:
I THINK WE'RE GONNA NEED IT.

265
00:13:45,325 --> 00:13:46,534
[ DOOR CHIMES ]

266
00:13:46,576 --> 00:13:47,868
ARCHER: COME IN.

267
00:13:50,747 --> 00:13:52,873
NICE CATCH.

268
00:13:52,915 --> 00:13:54,584
YOU'D MAKE A GOOD TWO-METER MAN.

269
00:13:54,626 --> 00:13:56,919
TOO BAD WE DON'T HAVE
A POOL ONBOARD.

270
00:13:56,961 --> 00:13:58,505
REED: A SHAME.

271
00:13:58,546 --> 00:14:01,090
A WIND STORM'S MOVING ACROSS
THE NORTHERN CONTINENT.

272
00:14:01,132 --> 00:14:02,925
LOOKS LIKE A NASTY ONE.

273
00:14:02,967 --> 00:14:04,010
ARCHER: SURVEY TEAM?

274
00:14:04,051 --> 00:14:05,219
REED: THEY'VE TAKEN SHELTER,

275
00:14:05,261 --> 00:14:06,763
BUT I'D RECOMMEND
PULLING THEM OUT.

276
00:14:06,805 --> 00:14:09,349
I'VE GOT A SHUTTLEPOD
ON STANDBY.

277
00:14:09,390 --> 00:14:10,308
[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]

278
00:14:10,350 --> 00:14:11,850
ARCHER: ARCHER TO T'POL.

279
00:14:11,892 --> 00:14:12,935
T'POL: YES, CAPTAIN.

280
00:14:12,977 --> 00:14:14,270
ARCHER: WHAT'S YOUR STATUS?

281
00:14:14,312 --> 00:14:16,105
T'POL: WE'VE RELOCATED
INTO A CAVERN.

282
00:14:16,147 --> 00:14:18,817
ARCHER: MR. REED THINKS
WE SHOULD COME DOWN AND GET YOU.

283
00:14:18,857 --> 00:14:22,278
T'POL: A LANDING UNDER THESE
CONDITIONS MIGHT BE DIFFICULT.

284
00:14:22,320 --> 00:14:24,280
WE'LL BE PROTECTED
UNTIL THE WINDS DIMINISH.

285
00:14:24,322 --> 00:14:26,240
ARCHER:
WE'LL KEEP AN EYE ON THE STORM.

286
00:14:26,282 --> 00:14:28,743
LET US KNOW
IF YOU NEED ANYTHING.

287
00:14:28,785 --> 00:14:31,204
T'POL: UNDERSTOOD.

288
00:14:31,245 --> 00:14:34,915
KEEP THE POD ON STANDBY,
JUST IN CASE.

289
00:14:34,957 --> 00:14:36,000
REED: AYE, SIR.

290
00:14:38,169 --> 00:14:40,588
TUCKER:
WHO'S GOT THE FOOD PACKS?

291
00:14:40,630 --> 00:14:41,881
CUTLER: UH, NOPE.

292
00:14:41,922 --> 00:14:42,923
TUCKER: TRAVIS?

293
00:14:42,965 --> 00:14:44,300
MAYWEATHER: NOT ME, SIR.

294
00:14:44,342 --> 00:14:47,011
T'POL: WE MUST'VE LEFT THEM
AT THE CAMPSITE.

295
00:14:47,053 --> 00:14:48,929
MAYWEATHER: I'LL GO.

296
00:14:48,971 --> 00:14:50,724
TUCKER: BE CAREFUL.

297
00:15:17,166 --> 00:15:18,585
MAYWEATHER: [ GRUNTS ]

298
00:15:27,009 --> 00:15:28,469
TRIP?!

299
00:15:36,561 --> 00:15:38,229
HELLO?!

300
00:15:42,024 --> 00:15:43,984
WAS ANYBODY OUTSIDE JUST NOW?

301
00:15:44,026 --> 00:15:46,112
TUCKER: JUST YOU. WHY?

302
00:15:46,153 --> 00:15:47,988
MAYWEATHER: THERE'S SOMEONE ELSE
OUT THERE.

303
00:15:48,030 --> 00:15:48,989
CUTLER: WHAT?

304
00:15:49,031 --> 00:15:51,534
MAYWEATHER: NEAR THE CAMPSITE.

305
00:15:51,576 --> 00:15:53,953
TUCKER: I THINK WE'VE HAD ENOUGH
GHOST STORIES FOR ONE NIGHT.

306
00:15:53,994 --> 00:15:55,580
MAYWEATHER: IT'S NO STORY.

307
00:15:55,622 --> 00:15:58,541
T'POL: WE'VE SCANNED THE PLANET.
IT'S UNINHABITED.

308
00:15:58,583 --> 00:16:00,835
MAYWEATHER: I'M TELLING YOU --
I SAW THREE PEOPLE.

309
00:16:00,877 --> 00:16:03,880
CUTLER: THREE?
WHAT DID THEY LOOK LIKE?

310
00:16:03,922 --> 00:16:05,214
MAYWEATHER: IT WAS TOO DARK.

311
00:16:05,256 --> 00:16:07,926
TUCKER: SUBCOMMANDER?

312
00:16:07,967 --> 00:16:09,552
T'POL:
OTHER THAN OURSELVES,

313
00:16:09,594 --> 00:16:11,554
THERE ARE NO HUMANOID
LIFE-FORMS HERE.

314
00:16:11,596 --> 00:16:13,556
MAYWEATHER: THERE COULD
BE SOMETHING WRONG
WITH YOUR SCANNER.

315
00:16:13,598 --> 00:16:15,141
T'POL: IT'S FUNCTIONING
PERFECTLY.

316
00:16:15,182 --> 00:16:17,184
PERHAPS YOU IMAGINED
SEEING THEM.

317
00:16:17,226 --> 00:16:19,896
MAYWEATHER: THEY LOOKED
PRETTY REAL TO ME.

318
00:16:20,939 --> 00:16:23,399
CUTLER: ETHAN?

319
00:16:23,441 --> 00:16:25,693
NOVAKOVICH: THERE'S SOMEONE
BACK THERE. I HEARD VOICES.

320
00:16:25,735 --> 00:16:28,404
ARE YOU GONNA TELL ME
I'M IMAGINING THINGS, TOO?

321
00:16:28,446 --> 00:16:29,948
IT'S NOT SAFE HERE.

322
00:16:29,989 --> 00:16:31,324
TUCKER: WE DON'T KNOW THAT.
THEY COULD BE FRIENDLY.

323
00:16:31,365 --> 00:16:32,575
NOVAKOVICH: THEN WHY
ARE THEY HIDING?

324
00:16:32,617 --> 00:16:34,201
WHY DON'T THEY COME OUT
AND SAY HELLO?

325
00:16:34,243 --> 00:16:35,662
WE SHOULD LEAVE!

326
00:16:35,703 --> 00:16:37,622
T'POL: WHERE DO YOU
PROPOSE WE GO?

327
00:16:37,664 --> 00:16:39,165
BACK OUT INTO THE STORM?

328
00:16:39,206 --> 00:16:40,834
NOVAKOVICH: IT'S BETTER
THAN BEING TRAPPED IN HERE.

329
00:16:40,875 --> 00:16:44,295
TUCKER: SLOW DOWN, CREWMAN.
THAT'S AN ORDER.

330
00:16:46,130 --> 00:16:47,298
MAYWEATHER: ETHAN!

331
00:16:49,258 --> 00:16:50,635
TUCKER: STAY HERE.

332
00:16:53,095 --> 00:16:54,889
TRAVIS.

333
00:17:05,024 --> 00:17:06,233
T'POL: I'LL BE BACK SHORTLY.

334
00:17:06,275 --> 00:17:07,944
CUTLER: WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

335
00:17:07,986 --> 00:17:12,532
T'POL: IF THERE'S SOMEONE BACK
THERE, I INTEND TO FIND THEM.

336
00:17:42,144 --> 00:17:44,146
MAYWEATHER: ETHAN!

337
00:17:53,447 --> 00:17:55,742
[ GROWLING ]

338
00:17:57,159 --> 00:17:59,913
TUCKER: TRAVIS!

339
00:17:59,954 --> 00:18:02,040
I SAW ONE!

340
00:18:03,624 --> 00:18:06,627
IT CAME RIGHT OUT OF THAT ROCK
LIKE IT WAS A PART OF IT.

341
00:18:06,669 --> 00:18:08,254
MAYWEATHER:
THAT COULD EXPLAIN WHY

342
00:18:08,295 --> 00:18:10,798
THEY'RE NOT SHOWING
UP ON OUR SCANNERS.

343
00:18:19,181 --> 00:18:21,642
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATION ]

344
00:18:48,086 --> 00:18:49,503
WHOA! OH!

345
00:18:54,300 --> 00:18:55,927
TUCKER: IT'S TOO DANGEROUS.

346
00:18:55,969 --> 00:18:57,470
WE SHOULD GO BACK.

347
00:19:00,514 --> 00:19:03,225
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATION ]

348
00:19:22,495 --> 00:19:25,039
CUTLER: WHO WERE THEY?

349
00:19:25,081 --> 00:19:26,707
T'POL: EXCUSE ME?

350
00:19:26,749 --> 00:19:30,003
CUTLER: WELL, WHO
WERE YOU TALKING TO?

351
00:19:30,044 --> 00:19:32,338
T'POL: TALKING TO?

352
00:19:32,379 --> 00:19:34,132
THERE'S NO ONE HERE.

353
00:19:37,259 --> 00:19:40,513
TUCKER: WE'VE LOST NOVAKOVICH,
AND WE'RE APPARENTLY NOT ALONE.

354
00:19:40,554 --> 00:19:42,556
THERE'S SOME KIND
OF LIFE-FORM DOWN HERE.

355
00:19:42,598 --> 00:19:44,642
ARCHER: CAN YOU MAKE IT BACK
TO THE CAVERN?

356
00:19:44,684 --> 00:19:46,727
TUCKER:
WE'RE HEADING THERE NOW, SIR.

357
00:19:49,563 --> 00:19:51,190
MAYWEATHER: THE CAPTAIN'S
ON HIS WAY.

358
00:19:51,231 --> 00:19:52,525
WE'RE GETTING OUT OF HERE.

359
00:19:52,566 --> 00:19:54,027
TUCKER:
NOT A MOMENT TOO SOON.

360
00:19:54,068 --> 00:19:57,279
FROM WHAT I SAW, THESE THINGS
LIVE INSIDE THE ROCK.

361
00:19:57,321 --> 00:20:00,074
T'POL: I PERFORMED
A GEOLOGICAL ANALYSIS.

362
00:20:00,116 --> 00:20:03,494
THE ROCKS ARE COMPOSED OF
LIMESTONE AND CORMALITE,

363
00:20:03,536 --> 00:20:04,704
NOTHING MORE.

364
00:20:04,745 --> 00:20:06,706
CUTLER:
SHE'S LYING, COMMANDER.

365
00:20:06,747 --> 00:20:08,332
I SAW HER TALKING TO THEM.

366
00:20:08,374 --> 00:20:10,376
TUCKER: CREWMAN?
CUTLER: IN THERE.

367
00:20:10,417 --> 00:20:12,170
THERE WERE TWO OF THEM.

368
00:20:12,211 --> 00:20:13,504
T'POL: SHE'S MISTAKEN.

369
00:20:13,546 --> 00:20:15,131
CUTLER: NO, I'M NOT.

370
00:20:15,173 --> 00:20:18,217
WHY WON'T YOU
TELL US WHAT'S GOING ON?

371
00:20:18,258 --> 00:20:19,969
WHAT DO THEY WANT?

372
00:20:23,222 --> 00:20:26,184
REED: I'VE GOT A FIX.
20 KILOMETERS NORTHEAST.

373
00:20:26,225 --> 00:20:27,185
[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]

374
00:20:27,226 --> 00:20:29,896
ARCHER: ARCHER TO NOVAKOVICH.

375
00:20:29,937 --> 00:20:32,065
ETHAN. RESPOND.

376
00:20:32,106 --> 00:20:33,191
NOVAKOVICH: WHO'S THERE?!

377
00:20:33,232 --> 00:20:34,859
WHO IS THAT?!

378
00:20:34,901 --> 00:20:36,402
ARCHER: THIS IS CAPTAIN ARCHER.
WE'RE ATTEMPTING TO LAND.

379
00:20:36,443 --> 00:20:38,404
I WANT YOU
TO GET BACK TO THE CAVERN.

380
00:20:38,445 --> 00:20:40,239
NOVAKOVICH: GO TO HELL!

381
00:20:43,409 --> 00:20:45,411
T'POL: I HAVE NO REASON
TO DECEIVE YOU.

382
00:20:45,452 --> 00:20:46,787
TUCKER: NEITHER DOES SHE.

383
00:20:46,829 --> 00:20:48,622
YOU KEEP CLAIMING THESE
CREATURES DON'T EXIST,

384
00:20:48,664 --> 00:20:50,791
BUT THE REST OF US
HAVE ALL SEEN THEM.

385
00:20:50,833 --> 00:20:52,585
THAT'S A LITTLE STRANGE,
DON'T YOU THINK?

386
00:20:52,626 --> 00:20:54,587
T'POL: I CAN'T EXPLAIN
WHAT YOU'VE SEEN,

387
00:20:54,628 --> 00:20:57,173
BUT I ASSURE YOU
I DIDN'T SPEAK TO ANYONE.

388
00:20:57,215 --> 00:20:59,008
TUCKER: I'D LIKE TO BELIEVE YOU,
BUT YOU VULCANS

389
00:20:59,050 --> 00:21:01,094
DON'T EXACTLY HAVE
A SPOTLESS TRACK RECORD

390
00:21:01,135 --> 00:21:03,221
WHEN IT COMES
TO BEING HONEST WITH US.

391
00:21:03,262 --> 00:21:04,972
T'POL: YOUR POINT?

392
00:21:05,014 --> 00:21:07,516
TUCKER: YOU'VE HELD THINGS
BACK BEFORE.

393
00:21:07,558 --> 00:21:09,769
YOU MIGHT BE DOING IT AGAIN.

394
00:21:09,810 --> 00:21:12,730
[ COMMUNICATOR BEEPS ]

395
00:21:12,772 --> 00:21:14,232
TUCKER HERE.

396
00:21:14,314 --> 00:21:16,109
ARCHER: WE'RE CLOSING IN
ON YOUR POSITION, TRIP.

397
00:21:16,150 --> 00:21:18,945
THERE'S A CLEARING A HUNDRED
METERS FROM THE CAVE ENTRANCE.

398
00:21:18,986 --> 00:21:20,696
GET TO IT.

399
00:21:27,327 --> 00:21:28,746
REED: I'M READING THEM.

400
00:21:28,788 --> 00:21:30,289
TWO KILOMETERS DUE WEST.

401
00:21:30,330 --> 00:21:32,583
ARCHER: I'M TAKING US DOWN.

402
00:21:39,298 --> 00:21:43,177
THERE'S A LOT OF WIND SHEAR
NEAR THE SURFACE.

403
00:21:43,219 --> 00:21:47,306
ACTIVATE THE AUXILIARY
LANDING THRUSTERS.

404
00:21:47,347 --> 00:21:49,850
ALTITUDE -- 70 METERS.

405
00:21:53,604 --> 00:21:55,064
40 METERS.

406
00:22:00,778 --> 00:22:03,656
I'LL HAVE TO TRY
A DIFFERENT VECTOR.

407
00:22:08,995 --> 00:22:10,246
REED: STARBOARD!

408
00:22:10,288 --> 00:22:11,330
ARCHER: I SEE IT.

409
00:22:15,793 --> 00:22:17,211
REED: THRUSTER FOUR'S DOWN.

410
00:22:17,253 --> 00:22:19,088
WE'RE LEAKING PLASMA COOLANT.

411
00:22:19,130 --> 00:22:20,464
ARCHER: ALMOST THERE.

412
00:22:20,506 --> 00:22:23,092
REED: SIR, WE CAN'T SAFELY
LAND IN THIS WIND

413
00:22:23,134 --> 00:22:24,260
WITH A THRUSTER OUT.

414
00:22:24,302 --> 00:22:27,972
[ ALARM BEEPS ]

415
00:22:28,014 --> 00:22:29,265
ARCHER: [ SIGHS ]

416
00:22:29,307 --> 00:22:31,267
[ COMMUNICATOR BEEPS ]

417
00:22:31,309 --> 00:22:32,768
ARCHER TO TUCKER.

418
00:22:32,810 --> 00:22:35,188
TUCKER: CAPTAIN, AREN'T YOU
FORGETTING SOMETHING?

419
00:22:35,229 --> 00:22:39,275
ARCHER: WE'RE GONNA HAVE TO WAIT
TILL THE WIND DIES DOWN.

420
00:22:39,317 --> 00:22:41,194
TRY TO MANAGE TILL THEN.

421
00:22:41,235 --> 00:22:42,528
TUCKER:
WE'LL DO OUR BEST, SIR.

422
00:22:42,569 --> 00:22:43,904
ARCHER: IF YOU RUN ACROSS

423
00:22:43,946 --> 00:22:46,157
ANY MORE OF THESE ALIENS,
TRY TO MAKE CONTACT.

424
00:22:46,199 --> 00:22:48,284
SEE WHAT YOU
CAN FIND OUT ABOUT THEM.

425
00:22:48,326 --> 00:22:50,077
TUCKER: UNDERSTOOD!

426
00:23:01,297 --> 00:23:02,798
CUTLER: UGH. [ PANTING ]

427
00:23:08,554 --> 00:23:10,056
MAYWEATHER: YOU OKAY?

428
00:23:10,097 --> 00:23:13,100
CUTLER: [ CHUCKLES ]
NEVER BETTER.

429
00:23:14,560 --> 00:23:16,145
TUCKER:
YOU HEARD THE CAPTAIN.

430
00:23:16,187 --> 00:23:18,814
HE WANTS TO KNOW
ABOUT YOUR FRIENDS.

431
00:23:18,856 --> 00:23:21,192
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA TELL HIM?

432
00:23:22,609 --> 00:23:24,528
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA TELL HIM?

433
00:23:28,157 --> 00:23:30,910
T'POL: THIS IS POINTLESS.
TUCKER: IS IT?

434
00:23:30,951 --> 00:23:32,870
WE'RE STUCK DOWN HERE
FOR GOD KNOWS HOW LONG

435
00:23:32,912 --> 00:23:35,039
WITH A BUNCH OF ROCK PEOPLE
WHO, FOR ALL WE KNOW,

436
00:23:35,081 --> 00:23:36,374
ARE STARING AT US
FROM THESE WALLS RIGHT NOW,

437
00:23:36,414 --> 00:23:37,958
NOT TO MENTION
A CREWMAN OUT THERE

438
00:23:38,000 --> 00:23:40,044
WHO PROBABLY
WON'T LAST THE NIGHT.

439
00:23:40,086 --> 00:23:41,461
NOW, IF WE'RE GONNA
GET THROUGH THIS,

440
00:23:41,503 --> 00:23:43,005
I NEED TO KNOW
WHAT THE HELL'S GOING ON.

441
00:23:43,047 --> 00:23:44,506
YOU BEGINNING TO SEE MY POINT?

442
00:23:44,548 --> 00:23:46,842
T'POL: I SHARE YOUR CONCERN
FOR CREWMAN NOVAKOVICH,

443
00:23:46,884 --> 00:23:48,135
BUT AS I TOLD YOU --

444
00:23:48,177 --> 00:23:49,303
TUCKER: YOU COULDN'T
CARE LESS ABOUT HIM

445
00:23:49,345 --> 00:23:50,846
OR ANY OF THE REST OF US!

446
00:23:50,888 --> 00:23:53,515
THAT'D REQUIRE SOME OF THOSE
USELESS HUMAN EMOTIONS.

447
00:23:53,557 --> 00:23:55,017
T'POL: YOUR EMOTIONS
ARE BEGINNING

448
00:23:55,059 --> 00:23:57,019
TO AFFECT YOUR JUDGMENT.

449
00:23:57,061 --> 00:23:58,896
YOU'RE BECOMING IRRATIONAL.

450
00:23:58,938 --> 00:24:02,858
TUCKER:
YOU'VE NEVER SEEN ME IRRATIONAL.

451
00:24:02,900 --> 00:24:04,860
MAYWEATHER: SIR, I HATE TO ADD
TO OUR PROBLEMS,

452
00:24:04,902 --> 00:24:06,528
BUT WE'RE RUNNING
LOW ON WATER.

453
00:24:06,570 --> 00:24:08,989
TUCKER: GREAT.

454
00:24:09,031 --> 00:24:11,158
WE'LL HAVE TO CONSERVE
WHAT'S LEFT.

455
00:24:11,200 --> 00:24:12,701
T'POL: THAT WON'T BE NECESSARY.

456
00:24:12,743 --> 00:24:15,621
I DETECTED WATER ABOUT
60 METERS IN THAT DIRECTION.

457
00:24:15,662 --> 00:24:17,039
TUCKER:
HOW DO WE KNOW YOU'RE NOT

458
00:24:17,081 --> 00:24:20,500
GOING IN THERE
TO TALK TO YOUR FRIENDS?

459
00:24:20,542 --> 00:24:22,711
T'POL: JOIN ME IF YOU'D LIKE.

460
00:24:22,753 --> 00:24:24,880
CUTLER: IT COULD BE A TRAP,
COMMANDER.

461
00:24:28,466 --> 00:24:31,553
T'POL: I CAN SURVIVE WITHOUT
WATER FOR SEVERAL DAYS.

462
00:24:31,595 --> 00:24:33,847
CAN YOU?

463
00:24:34,807 --> 00:24:36,976
TUCKER: SIT DOWN.

464
00:24:38,602 --> 00:24:41,063
YOU HEARD ME.

465
00:24:53,575 --> 00:24:55,535
ARCHER: HOW'S HE DOING?

466
00:24:55,577 --> 00:24:56,578
SATO: NOT GOOD.

467
00:24:56,620 --> 00:24:58,538
HIS BIO-SIGNS ARE VERY ERRATIC.

468
00:24:58,580 --> 00:24:59,623
ARCHER: TRY HIM AGAIN.

469
00:24:59,665 --> 00:25:02,001
HOCHI:<i> ENTERPRISE</i> TO NOVAKOVICH.

470
00:25:02,042 --> 00:25:03,585
CAN YOU HEAR ME?

471
00:25:03,627 --> 00:25:05,963
ETHAN?

472
00:25:06,005 --> 00:25:08,299
NOVAKOVICH: [SCREAMING]

473
00:25:11,677 --> 00:25:15,055
ARCHER: MR. REED,
CAN YOU GET A LOCK ON HIM?

474
00:25:15,097 --> 00:25:16,182
REED: YES, SIR.

475
00:25:16,223 --> 00:25:17,599
ARCHER:
LOOKS LIKE OUR ONLY CHOICE.

476
00:25:17,641 --> 00:25:19,393
REED: UNDERSTOOD. STAND BY.

477
00:25:23,605 --> 00:25:25,024
THERE'S A PROBLEM, SIR.

478
00:25:25,065 --> 00:25:27,525
THERE ARE CONTAMINANTS
IN THE MATTER STREAM.

479
00:25:27,567 --> 00:25:31,571
THE PHASE DISCRIMINATOR CAN'T
SEEM TO ISOLATE THE DEBRIS.

480
00:25:34,241 --> 00:25:35,826
NOVAKOVICH: [ GROANS ]

481
00:25:35,868 --> 00:25:37,953
REED: REED TO SICK BAY.

482
00:25:37,995 --> 00:25:40,498
MEDICAL EMERGENCY.

483
00:25:40,538 --> 00:25:43,583
TUCKER:
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

484
00:25:43,625 --> 00:25:45,461
T'POL: WORKING.

485
00:25:45,503 --> 00:25:47,505
TUCKER: ON WHAT?

486
00:25:47,545 --> 00:25:49,798
T'POL: SCANS I TOOK
THIS AFTERNOON.

487
00:25:49,840 --> 00:25:52,176
TUCKER: FIND ANYTHING YOU WANT
TO TELL ME ABOUT?

488
00:25:52,218 --> 00:25:54,053
T'POL: THERE'S NOTHING
OF SCIENTIFIC INTEREST

489
00:25:54,094 --> 00:25:55,221
ON THIS PLANET.

490
00:25:55,262 --> 00:25:56,638
OUR MISSION HERE
WAS A WASTE OF TIME.

491
00:25:56,680 --> 00:26:00,600
TUCKER: THAT'S WHAT
YOU'D LIKE US TO THINK.

492
00:26:00,642 --> 00:26:02,311
LET ME SEE THAT THING.

493
00:26:02,353 --> 00:26:03,603
T'POL: THE READINGS
ARE IN VULCAN.

494
00:26:03,645 --> 00:26:05,398
YOU WON'T UNDERSTAND.

495
00:26:05,439 --> 00:26:08,734
TUCKER: NO, BUT HOSHI WOULD.

496
00:26:08,775 --> 00:26:10,652
THIS COULD BE EVIDENCE.

497
00:26:10,694 --> 00:26:12,654
T'POL: OF WHAT?

498
00:26:12,696 --> 00:26:14,323
TUCKER: YOUR LITTLE CONSPIRACY.

499
00:26:14,365 --> 00:26:18,327
T'POL: I WAS WRONG. THERE 
IS SOMETHING OF INTEREST HERE.

500
00:26:18,369 --> 00:26:21,372
I'VE LEARNED A GREAT DEAL
ABOUT HUMAN BEHAVIOR.

501
00:26:21,414 --> 00:26:22,664
TUCKER: OH?

502
00:26:22,706 --> 00:26:24,582
T'POL: UNDER STRESS,
YOU BECOME VOLATILE.

503
00:26:24,624 --> 00:26:26,168
YOU'RE A FAR MORE
DANGEROUS SPECIES

504
00:26:26,210 --> 00:26:27,753
THAN I PREVIOUSLY BELIEVED.

505
00:26:27,794 --> 00:26:29,046
TUCKER: YOUR PEOPLE HAVE BEEN
TELLING US THAT KIND OF CRAP

506
00:26:29,088 --> 00:26:30,923
FOR A HUNDRED YEARS!

507
00:26:30,964 --> 00:26:32,425
LOOKS LIKE YOU FINALLY FOUND

508
00:26:32,466 --> 00:26:34,343
A WAY TO PUT US
BACK IN OUR CAGE.

509
00:26:34,385 --> 00:26:35,635
MAYWEATHER: SIR?

510
00:26:35,677 --> 00:26:37,179
TUCKER: IMAGINE THE NEWS
BACK HOME, TRAVIS!

511
00:26:37,221 --> 00:26:41,308
<i>ENTERPRISE</i> CREW FOUND DEAD!

512
00:26:41,350 --> 00:26:44,228
SIX WEEKS INTO
THEIR HISTORIC VOYAGE,

513
00:26:44,270 --> 00:26:46,230
THE BODIES OF
ALL 82 CREW MEMBERS

514
00:26:46,272 --> 00:26:48,357
WERE LOCATED
ON AN UNINHABITED WORLD.

515
00:26:48,399 --> 00:26:51,151
A VULCAN SHIP MADE
THE UNFORTUNATE DISCOVERY.

516
00:26:51,193 --> 00:26:54,654
CAUSE OF DEATH
REMAINS A MYSTERY.

517
00:26:54,696 --> 00:26:55,822
BUT WHAT VULCANS WON'T SAY

518
00:26:55,864 --> 00:26:57,575
IS THEY KNOW EXACTLY
WHO ATTACKED US!

519
00:26:57,615 --> 00:26:59,493
IN FACT, THEY ARRANGED
THE WHOLE THING!

520
00:26:59,535 --> 00:27:02,662
THEY LURED US DOWN HERE SO THEY
COULD SABOTAGE OUR MISSION!

521
00:27:02,704 --> 00:27:05,207
MAYWEATHER: YOU WERE THE ONE
WHO FOUND THESE CAVES,

522
00:27:05,249 --> 00:27:08,085
AND IT WAS YOUR IDEA
TO STAY OVERNIGHT.

523
00:27:08,127 --> 00:27:11,213
T'POL: I DIDN'T ASK
YOU OR MR. TUCKER TO JOIN US.

524
00:27:11,255 --> 00:27:13,048
TUCKER:
WE KNOW YOU'RE HERE!

525
00:27:13,090 --> 00:27:15,717
WHY DON'T YOU SHOW YOURSELVES?

526
00:27:15,759 --> 00:27:17,386
YOU'RE NOT AFRAID
OF US, ARE YOU?

527
00:27:17,428 --> 00:27:19,096
T'POL: THERE'S NO ONE THERE,
COMMANDER.

528
00:27:19,138 --> 00:27:21,140
TUCKER: MAYBE YOU'RE WAITING
FOR THE OTHERS TO COME DOWN,

529
00:27:21,181 --> 00:27:22,891
SO YOU CAN KILL US ALL AT ONCE!

530
00:27:22,933 --> 00:27:24,726
DID YOU SEE THAT?!

531
00:27:24,768 --> 00:27:27,563
T'POL: ALL I SEE
IS A DELUSIONAL ENGINEER!

532
00:27:28,814 --> 00:27:30,190
TUCKER:
SOUNDS LIKE YOU'RE GETTING

533
00:27:30,232 --> 00:27:32,192
A LITTLE VOLATILE
YOURSELF, SUBCOMMANDER.

534
00:27:32,234 --> 00:27:36,238
I THOUGHT YOU HAD YOUR EMOTIONS
ALL LOCKED UP.

535
00:27:36,280 --> 00:27:37,739
HAVING A LITTLE PROBLEM,
ARE YOU?

536
00:27:37,781 --> 00:27:41,285
MAYWEATHER: COMMANDER, THERE!

537
00:27:41,327 --> 00:27:44,497
YOU THINK WE'RE GONNA
WAIT AROUND HERE FOR
YOU TO SLAUGHTER US?

538
00:27:44,538 --> 00:27:47,749
I'LL BLOW THIS WHOLE CAVE APART
IF I HAVE TO!

539
00:27:47,791 --> 00:27:51,211
I KNOW YOU HEAR ME!

540
00:27:53,964 --> 00:27:56,800
PHLOX: HUMAN SKIN
IS A RESILIENT ORGAN.

541
00:27:56,842 --> 00:27:58,969
THESE WOUNDS
SHOULD HEAL NICELY.

542
00:27:59,011 --> 00:28:00,804
ARCHER: CAN I TALK TO HIM?

543
00:28:00,846 --> 00:28:03,641
PHLOX: YES, BUT I DOUBT
HE'LL MAKE MUCH SENSE.

544
00:28:03,681 --> 00:28:05,725
HAVE YOU EVER HEARD
OF TROPOLISINE?

545
00:28:05,767 --> 00:28:07,436
ARCHER: NO.
PHLOX: MM.

546
00:28:07,478 --> 00:28:08,770
IT'S A PSYCHOTROPIC COMPOUND

547
00:28:08,812 --> 00:28:11,190
KNOWN FOR ITS
HALLUCINOGENIC EFFECTS.

548
00:28:11,231 --> 00:28:14,234
THIS CREWMAN'S BLOODSTREAM
IS FILLED WITH IT.

549
00:28:14,276 --> 00:28:16,028
ARCHER: IF IT WAS DOWN
ON THE PLANET,

550
00:28:16,069 --> 00:28:18,113
WHY DIDN'T OUR SENSORS
PICK IT UP?

551
00:28:18,155 --> 00:28:20,366
PHLOX: NORMALLY IT'S FOUND
IN CERTAIN FLOWERING PLANTS.

552
00:28:20,407 --> 00:28:22,660
PERHAPS YOUR SENSORS WEREN'T
CALIBRATED TO DETECT IT.

553
00:28:22,700 --> 00:28:25,871
REED: OR PERHAPS IT WASN'T THERE
UNTIL THAT DAMN WIND STARTED.

554
00:28:25,912 --> 00:28:27,747
ARCHER: HOW LONG WILL
THE EFFECTS LAST?

555
00:28:27,789 --> 00:28:29,416
PHLOX: NOW THAT HE'S BACK
ON<i> ENTERPRISE,</i>

556
00:28:29,458 --> 00:28:31,877
HE SHOULD BE ALL RIGHT
IN THREE OR FOUR HOURS.

557
00:28:31,918 --> 00:28:35,506
ARCHER: WILL THIS TRO--
PHLOX: TROPOLISINE.

558
00:28:35,548 --> 00:28:37,715
ARCHER: WILL IT AFFECT
T'POL AS WELL?

559
00:28:37,757 --> 00:28:38,800
PHLOX:
THERE'S NO WAY TO KNOW.

560
00:28:38,842 --> 00:28:40,010
IT MIGHT AFFECT HER

561
00:28:40,052 --> 00:28:42,846
TO A LESSER DEGREE
OR A GREATER DEGREE.

562
00:28:46,808 --> 00:28:48,686
ARCHER: ARCHER TO T'POL.

563
00:28:48,727 --> 00:28:51,063
T'POL: YES, CAPTAIN?

564
00:28:51,104 --> 00:28:53,065
ARCHER: WE HAVE NOVAKOVICH.

565
00:28:53,106 --> 00:28:56,151
T'POL: AND I HAVE A PHASE PISTOL
POINTED AT MY HEAD.

566
00:28:56,193 --> 00:28:57,736
ARCHER: WHAT?

567
00:28:57,777 --> 00:29:00,030
TUCKER: MY SUSPICIONS WERE
RIGHT ON THE NOSE, CAPTAIN.

568
00:29:00,072 --> 00:29:01,323
OUR LITTLE VULCAN HERE

569
00:29:01,365 --> 00:29:03,367
IS NOT WHAT SHE APPEARS TO BE --
NEVER WAS.

570
00:29:03,409 --> 00:29:05,703
ARCHER: WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

571
00:29:05,744 --> 00:29:07,413
TUCKER: THERE'S SOME KIND
OF CREATURES DOWN HERE.

572
00:29:07,454 --> 00:29:08,622
THEY HIDE INSIDE SOLID ROCK.

573
00:29:08,664 --> 00:29:10,082
TRAVIS AND I
HAVE BOTH SEEN THEM.

574
00:29:10,123 --> 00:29:12,376
CUTLER SAW TWO OF THEM
TALKING TO T'POL.

575
00:29:12,418 --> 00:29:14,503
THEY'RE UP TO SOMETHING,
BUT OF COURSE, SHE DENIES IT.

576
00:29:14,545 --> 00:29:16,004
ARCHER: LISTEN TO ME.

577
00:29:16,046 --> 00:29:20,092
YOU'VE ALL BEEN EXPOSED
TO A PSYCHOTROPIC COMPOUND.

578
00:29:20,133 --> 00:29:22,511
IT CAUSES HEIGHTENED ANXIETY,
HALLUCINATIONS.

579
00:29:22,553 --> 00:29:24,846
TUCKER: ARE YOU TELLING ME
THOSE CREATURES AREN'T REAL?

580
00:29:24,888 --> 00:29:27,766
ARCHER: THE COMPOUND COMES
FROM THE POLLEN OF A FLOWER.

581
00:29:27,807 --> 00:29:29,809
WE THINK IT WAS BLOWN DOWN
FROM THE MOUNTAINS

582
00:29:29,851 --> 00:29:31,061
WHEN THE WINDS STARTED.

583
00:29:31,103 --> 00:29:32,854
THE DOCTOR'S RUN TESTS
ON NOVAKOVICH.

584
00:29:32,896 --> 00:29:35,649
HE THINKS HE'S GONNA
BE OKAY IN A FEW HOURS.

585
00:29:35,691 --> 00:29:38,902
SO IF YOU CAN GET AS DEEP
AS YOU CAN INTO THE CAVES,

586
00:29:38,944 --> 00:29:41,405
YOUR SYMPTOMS SHOULD DISSIPATE
AROUND THE SAME TIME.

587
00:29:41,447 --> 00:29:43,865
TUCKER:
WE DIDN'T IMAGINE THIS, CAPTAIN.

588
00:29:43,907 --> 00:29:45,284
ARCHER:
YOU DEALT WITH SIMULATIONS

589
00:29:45,325 --> 00:29:48,078
VERY CLOSE TO THIS
IN STARFLEET TRAINING.

590
00:29:48,120 --> 00:29:50,372
YOU'RE FAMILIAR
WITH MIND-ALTERING AGENTS.

591
00:29:50,414 --> 00:29:53,083
WE'LL BE DOWN TO GET YOU
AS SOON AS THE WINDS LET UP.

592
00:29:53,125 --> 00:29:54,501
TUCKER:
YOU'RE NOT HERE, CAPTAIN.

593
00:29:54,543 --> 00:29:56,712
YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND
WHAT'S GOING ON.

594
00:29:56,754 --> 00:29:59,923
ARCHER: PUT YOUR WEAPON DOWN,
TRIP. THAT'S AN ORDER.

595
00:30:03,969 --> 00:30:05,304
T'POL?

596
00:30:05,345 --> 00:30:07,180
T'POL: HE'S LOWERED
HIS PHASE PISTOL, SIR.

597
00:30:07,222 --> 00:30:08,515
ARCHER:
HAVE YOU BEEN AFFECTED?

598
00:30:08,557 --> 00:30:10,309
T'POL: YES, BUT ONLY SLIGHTLY.

599
00:30:10,350 --> 00:30:14,104
ARCHER:
TRY TO HOLD ON. ARCHER OUT.

600
00:30:14,146 --> 00:30:17,691
GET TO THE BRIDGE.
I WANT A WEATHER REPORT.

601
00:30:29,035 --> 00:30:30,996
TUCKER: TRAVIS.

602
00:30:31,037 --> 00:30:33,457
YOU STILL WITH ME?

603
00:30:33,499 --> 00:30:35,083
I NEED YOU ON YOUR FEET.

604
00:30:35,125 --> 00:30:39,004
THOSE THINGS COULD COME BACK
AT ANY TIME.

605
00:30:39,045 --> 00:30:40,339
LISTEN TO ME.

606
00:30:40,380 --> 00:30:42,966
I'M GIVING YOU AN ORDER.

607
00:30:45,010 --> 00:30:47,763
WHAT'S WRONG?

608
00:30:47,805 --> 00:30:49,515
ENSIGN?

609
00:30:51,057 --> 00:30:52,976
WHAT'D YOU DO TO HIM?

610
00:30:56,563 --> 00:30:58,565
I CAN SEE WHY YOU GET ALONG
SO WELL WITH THEM.

611
00:30:58,607 --> 00:31:00,275
SNEAKING AROUND
IN THE SHADOWS --

612
00:31:00,317 --> 00:31:02,902
THAT'S SECOND NATURE
TO YOU VULCANS, ISN'T IT?

613
00:31:02,944 --> 00:31:04,988
T'POL: [ SPEAKS VULCAN ]

614
00:31:05,030 --> 00:31:07,115
TUCKER: I HAVE NO IDEA
WHAT YOU JUST SAID,

615
00:31:07,157 --> 00:31:10,494
BUT IT DIDN'T SOUND VERY NICE.

616
00:31:10,536 --> 00:31:12,954
YOU'RE MAKING A MISTAKE
WORKING WITH HER.

617
00:31:12,996 --> 00:31:16,500
SHE'LL STAB YOU IN THE BACK
FIRST CHANCE SHE GETS.

618
00:31:19,127 --> 00:31:21,963
TELL YOU WHAT.

619
00:31:22,005 --> 00:31:26,092
COME OUT, AND WE'LL SETTLE THIS
PEACEFULLY.

620
00:31:26,134 --> 00:31:29,304
WHATEVER SHE TOLD YOU
ABOUT HUMANS --

621
00:31:29,346 --> 00:31:32,015
IT'S NOT TRUE.

622
00:31:32,057 --> 00:31:34,100
YOU CAN SEE FOR YOURSELF.

623
00:31:34,142 --> 00:31:36,562
SAY SOMETHING!

624
00:31:37,813 --> 00:31:40,649
[ PANTING ]

625
00:31:46,405 --> 00:31:48,574
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

626
00:31:51,117 --> 00:31:52,452
YES, SIR.

627
00:31:52,494 --> 00:31:55,288
I KNOW, I KNOW,

628
00:31:55,330 --> 00:31:57,708
BUT THEY'RE NOT
GIVING ME MUCH CHOICE.

629
00:31:57,750 --> 00:32:00,960
I GOT TO PROTECT MY CREW.

630
00:32:01,002 --> 00:32:04,423
I UNDERSTAND, MR. VELIK,
BUT I CAN'T DO THAT.

631
00:32:04,464 --> 00:32:06,049
THEY'RE TRYING TO KILL US.

632
00:32:08,719 --> 00:32:10,429
NICE TRY.

633
00:32:10,470 --> 00:32:12,765
T'POL: [ SPEAKS VULCAN ]

634
00:32:16,643 --> 00:32:19,271
REED: THE CENTER OF THE STORM
HAS ALREADY PASSED OVER THEM,

635
00:32:19,312 --> 00:32:21,565
BUT THE SYSTEM SPANS
SOME 500 KILOMETERS.

636
00:32:21,607 --> 00:32:23,734
WE WON'T BE ABLE TO LAND
A SHUTTLEPOD BEFORE DAWN.

637
00:32:23,776 --> 00:32:25,694
ARCHER: WHEN'S THAT?
REED: NINE HOURS.

638
00:32:25,736 --> 00:32:27,195
PHLOX:
PHLOX TO CAPTAIN ARCHER.

639
00:32:27,237 --> 00:32:28,822
ARCHER: GO AHEAD.

640
00:32:28,864 --> 00:32:31,575
PHLOX: PLEASE REPORT TO SICK BAY
IMMEDIATELY. IT'S URGENT.

641
00:32:34,661 --> 00:32:38,039
ARCHER: I THOUGHT YOU SAID
HE WAS GONNA BE FINE.

642
00:32:39,875 --> 00:32:42,085
PHLOX: I DID.

643
00:32:42,127 --> 00:32:45,672
BUT EACH TROPOLISINE ATOM
CONTAINS A STRAY NEUTRON.

644
00:32:45,714 --> 00:32:48,425
WHEN IT STARTED TO BREAK DOWN
IN HIS BLOODSTREAM,

645
00:32:48,467 --> 00:32:50,385
IT RELEASED
AN UNDETECTABLE TOXIN.

646
00:32:50,427 --> 00:32:52,846
I'VE INJECTED HIM
WITH INAPROVALINE,

647
00:32:52,888 --> 00:32:57,476
BUT I...THINK
IT MAY BE TOO LATE.

648
00:32:57,517 --> 00:32:58,936
IF I'D RUN A SUBMOLECULAR SCAN,

649
00:32:58,977 --> 00:33:01,146
I MIGHT HAVE ANTICIPATED
THE COMPLICATION,

650
00:33:01,187 --> 00:33:03,356
BUT THERE WAS NO REASON TO.

651
00:33:03,398 --> 00:33:07,736
AT LEAST,
THERE DIDN'T SEEM TO BE.

652
00:33:07,778 --> 00:33:12,324
I CAN'T TELL YOU
HOW SORRY I AM, CAPTAIN.

653
00:33:12,365 --> 00:33:14,660
ARCHER:
WHAT ABOUT THE OTHERS?

654
00:33:14,701 --> 00:33:16,995
PHLOX: THEY SPENT LESS TIME
EXPOSED TO THE POLLEN.

655
00:33:17,036 --> 00:33:21,082
ARCHER: I'VE GOT FOUR PEOPLE
DOWN ON THE SURFACE, DOCTOR!

656
00:33:21,124 --> 00:33:22,960
I NEED TO KNOW
IF THEY'RE GONNA BE DEAD

657
00:33:23,001 --> 00:33:25,253
WHEN WE GET THERE
IN THE MORNING.

658
00:33:46,024 --> 00:33:47,442
TUCKER: STAY AWAKE, TRAVIS.

659
00:33:47,484 --> 00:33:50,946
CAN'T AFFORD TO HAVE
YOU GOING OUT ON ME!

660
00:33:50,988 --> 00:33:53,532
MAYWEATHER: I'M...TRYING, SIR.

661
00:33:53,573 --> 00:33:56,493
TRUCKER: CUTLER, YOU OKAY?
CUTLER: [ GROANS ]

662
00:33:59,245 --> 00:34:00,998
TUCKER: IF YOU'RE WAITING
FOR ME TO PASS OUT,

663
00:34:01,039 --> 00:34:02,541
YOU'RE WASTING YOUR TIME.

664
00:34:02,582 --> 00:34:04,001
YOU MIGHT AS WELL
HAVE YOUR FRIENDS

665
00:34:04,042 --> 00:34:06,545
COME OUT NOW AND DO WHATEVER
THEY'RE GONNA DO.

666
00:34:06,586 --> 00:34:08,588
[ COMMUNICATOR BEEPS ]

667
00:34:08,630 --> 00:34:11,008
T'POL: T'POL.

668
00:34:11,049 --> 00:34:11,967
ARCHER: HOW ARE YOU DOING?

669
00:34:12,009 --> 00:34:13,510
TUCKER: WHO'S THAT?

670
00:34:13,552 --> 00:34:15,929
ARCHER: IT'S THE CAPTAIN, TRIP.
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

671
00:34:15,971 --> 00:34:17,347
T'POL: HE'S IRRATIONAL, SIR.

672
00:34:17,389 --> 00:34:20,266
MAYWEATHER AND CUTLER
ARE NEARLY UNCONSCIOUS.

673
00:34:20,308 --> 00:34:23,020
ARCHER: BOTH OF YOU LISTEN
TO ME VERY CAREFULLY.

674
00:34:23,061 --> 00:34:24,396
NOVAKOVICH MAY BE DYING.

675
00:34:24,437 --> 00:34:27,607
TURNS OUT THE POLLEN
CONTAINS SOME KIND OF TOXIN

676
00:34:27,649 --> 00:34:29,401
OUR SENSORS HADN'T DETECTED.

677
00:34:29,442 --> 00:34:31,069
HE'S RESPONDING TO MEDICATION,

678
00:34:31,110 --> 00:34:35,198
BUT HIS ODDS OF RECOVERY WOULD
BE A HELL OF A LOT BETTER

679
00:34:35,240 --> 00:34:37,034
IF WE'D TREATED HIM SOONER.

680
00:34:37,075 --> 00:34:38,952
THE DOCTOR AND MALCOLM

681
00:34:38,994 --> 00:34:41,955
ARE SYNTHESIZING AMPOULES
OF INAPROVALINE.

682
00:34:41,997 --> 00:34:44,833
WE'RE GONNA HAVE TO USE THE
TRANSPORTER TO GET IT TO YOU,

683
00:34:44,875 --> 00:34:46,626
BUT IT'S IMPERATIVE

684
00:34:46,668 --> 00:34:48,837
THAT YOU INOCULATE YOURSELVES
AS SOON AS POSSIBLE.

685
00:34:48,879 --> 00:34:50,881
DO YOU UNDERSTAND
WHAT I'M SAYING?

686
00:34:50,923 --> 00:34:52,841
TUCKER: TAKING AN INJECTION
ISN'T GONNA CHANGE A DAMN THING!

687
00:34:52,883 --> 00:34:54,217
DON'T YOU SEE THAT?

688
00:34:54,259 --> 00:34:56,094
THEY'RE PLANNING
SOMETHING, CAPTAIN --

689
00:34:56,135 --> 00:34:57,596
FIRST US, THEN ALL OF YOU!

690
00:34:57,637 --> 00:34:59,305
[ CONVERSATION IN VULCAN ]

691
00:35:05,186 --> 00:35:06,646
ARCHER:
WHAT'S GOING ON, HOSHI?

692
00:35:06,688 --> 00:35:07,940
SATO: SHE SAYS TRIP
IS GONNA KILL HER,

693
00:35:07,981 --> 00:35:10,191
AND I DON'T THINK
SHE'S IMAGINING IT.

694
00:35:10,233 --> 00:35:12,569
TUCKER: SAY ONE MORE WORD OF
THAT GIBBERISH, AND I'M GONNA
SPLIT YOU IN TWO!

695
00:35:12,611 --> 00:35:14,613
ARCHER: TRIP, LISTEN TO ME.

696
00:35:14,654 --> 00:35:17,282
THE POLLEN'S AFFECTING HER, TOO.

697
00:35:17,323 --> 00:35:19,534
THINK ABOUT IT.

698
00:35:19,576 --> 00:35:21,912
YOU'VE HEARD OF PEOPLE
SUFFERING FROM DEMENTIA

699
00:35:21,954 --> 00:35:23,956
WHO REVERT
TO THEIR NATIVE LANGUAGE.

700
00:35:23,997 --> 00:35:25,832
SHE CAN'T HELP IT.

701
00:35:25,874 --> 00:35:27,918
TUCKER: THE ONLY THING
THAT'S AFFECTING HER
ARE THOSE ROCK PEOPLE.

702
00:35:27,960 --> 00:35:30,629
IF I CAN STOP HER NOW,
I CAN SAVE<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

703
00:35:30,670 --> 00:35:33,006
ARCHER: TRIP, HOW LONG
HAVE WE KNOWN EACH OTHER?

704
00:35:33,048 --> 00:35:35,050
TUCKER: WHAT'S THAT GOT TO DO
WITH ANYTHING?

705
00:35:35,092 --> 00:35:38,845
ARCHER: REMEMBER WHEN YOUR
E.V. PACK FROZE UP ON TITAN

706
00:35:38,887 --> 00:35:41,347
DURING THE OMEGA
TRAINING MISSION?

707
00:35:41,389 --> 00:35:43,516
YOU GOT NITROGEN NARCOSIS.

708
00:35:43,558 --> 00:35:45,602
YOU STARTED TO TRY
TO TAKE OFF YOUR HELMET.

709
00:35:45,644 --> 00:35:47,646
YOU REMEMBER
WHAT I'M TALKING ABOUT?

710
00:35:47,687 --> 00:35:49,064
TUCKER: WHAT'S YOUR POINT?!

711
00:35:49,106 --> 00:35:51,483
ARCHER: I ORDERED YOU
TO KEEP YOUR HELMET ON.

712
00:35:51,524 --> 00:35:53,819
YOU WERE DELIRIOUS,
THOUGHT YOU WERE GONNA DIE,

713
00:35:53,860 --> 00:35:56,362
BUT YOU OBEYED THAT ORDER
BECAUSE YOU TRUSTED ME.

714
00:35:56,404 --> 00:36:00,492
I'M ASKING YOU TO TRUST ME NOW.

715
00:36:00,533 --> 00:36:02,619
TAKE THE INJECTION.

716
00:36:02,661 --> 00:36:07,082
THEN WE'LL DEAL
WITH THESE ROCK PEOPLE.

717
00:36:15,173 --> 00:36:17,467
TUCKER: TOO LATE, CAPTAIN!

718
00:36:17,509 --> 00:36:20,178
I'M NOT GONNA DIE
WITH A HYPOSPRAY IN MY HAND.

719
00:36:20,219 --> 00:36:21,346
ARCHER: TRIP.

720
00:36:21,387 --> 00:36:23,556
TUCKER: NO!
IT'S NOT GONNA HAPPEN!

721
00:36:23,598 --> 00:36:26,768
ARCHER: ALL RIGHT.
FORGET THE MEDICINE.

722
00:36:26,810 --> 00:36:31,898
I THINK IT'S TIME I EXPLAIN
WHAT'S REALLY GOING ON...

723
00:36:33,191 --> 00:36:35,110
BUT JUST STAND BY FOR A MINUTE.

724
00:36:35,152 --> 00:36:37,612
I NEED MALCOLM
TO TARGET YOUR POSITION.

725
00:36:37,654 --> 00:36:39,990
THEN I'LL GIVE YOU YOUR ORDERS.

726
00:36:44,744 --> 00:36:47,288
ARCHER TO PHLOX.
THE SOONER THE BETTER.

727
00:36:47,330 --> 00:36:48,581
PHLOX: UNDERSTOOD.

728
00:36:48,623 --> 00:36:51,334
HOW CLOSE CAN YOU GET IT?

729
00:36:51,376 --> 00:36:52,794
REED: I THINK I CAN
SAFELY PLACE IT

730
00:36:52,836 --> 00:36:54,171
TWO METERS INSIDE
THE MOUTH OF THE CAVE.

731
00:36:54,212 --> 00:36:55,254
PHLOX: GOOD.

732
00:36:59,051 --> 00:37:01,761
TUCKER: CAPTAIN!

733
00:37:01,803 --> 00:37:03,471
HELLO?

734
00:37:03,513 --> 00:37:07,142
I'M WAITING FOR THAT ORDER,
BUT I CAN'T WAIT MUCH LONGER!

735
00:37:09,227 --> 00:37:11,437
ARCHER: ALL RIGHT, TRIP.

736
00:37:11,479 --> 00:37:14,191
THIS IS
A MAJOR BREACH OF SECURITY,

737
00:37:14,273 --> 00:37:17,402
BUT I'M GOING
TO HAVE TO TRUST YOU.

738
00:37:17,443 --> 00:37:18,444
TUCKER: GO AHEAD.

739
00:37:18,486 --> 00:37:19,946
ARCHER:
STARFLEET SENT US HERE

740
00:37:19,988 --> 00:37:23,533
TO MAKE CONTACT
WITH A SILICON-BASED LIFE-FORM.

741
00:37:23,575 --> 00:37:26,411
T'POL WAS THE ONLY PERSON
GRANTED CLEARANCE

742
00:37:26,452 --> 00:37:27,620
TO SPEAK WITH THEM.

743
00:37:27,662 --> 00:37:29,789
IT SEEMS
THEY'VE MET VULCANS BEFORE.

744
00:37:29,831 --> 00:37:31,833
TUCKER:
WHY COULDN'T YOU TELL ME THAT?

745
00:37:31,875 --> 00:37:35,170
ARCHER: WHEN A MISSION'S
CLASSIFIED TOP-SECRET,
I DON'T ASK WHY.

746
00:37:35,212 --> 00:37:36,755
TUCKER:
IF IT WAS SO TOP-SECRET,

747
00:37:36,796 --> 00:37:39,257
THEN WHY'D YOU LET US ALL
COME DOWN TO THE SURFACE --

748
00:37:39,298 --> 00:37:40,967
LET US SPEND THE NIGHT?

749
00:37:41,009 --> 00:37:43,220
SATO: THE WINDS.

750
00:37:43,261 --> 00:37:47,306
ARCHER: WE NEVER THOUGHT
THE STORM WOULD DRIVE YOU
INTO THE CAVES.

751
00:37:47,348 --> 00:37:49,684
THAT'S WHERE
THESE ROCK PEOPLE LIVE.

752
00:37:49,726 --> 00:37:52,854
THEY DIDN'T WANT ANYBODY
IN THERE EXCEPT FOR T'POL,

753
00:37:52,896 --> 00:37:55,190
SO THEY'RE NOT TOO HAPPY
RIGHT NOW.

754
00:37:55,232 --> 00:37:57,150
I'M SURE YOU CAN
UNDERSTAND THAT.

755
00:37:57,192 --> 00:38:01,071
THEY'VE EVEN THREATENED
TO DESTROY<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

756
00:38:01,113 --> 00:38:03,823
NOW, T'POL
NEEDS TO EXPLAIN TO THEM

757
00:38:03,865 --> 00:38:05,158
WHY YOU'RE ALL THERE,

758
00:38:05,200 --> 00:38:07,285
BUT SHE'S NOT
GONNA HAVE MUCH CREDIBILITY

759
00:38:07,326 --> 00:38:10,247
WITH YOU POINTING
A PHASE PISTOL AT HER.

760
00:38:10,288 --> 00:38:12,165
IF THEY AGREE TO LISTEN TO HER,

761
00:38:12,207 --> 00:38:14,709
YOU'LL NEED
TO LOWER YOUR WEAPON.

762
00:38:14,751 --> 00:38:16,878
IF THEY DON'T...

763
00:38:16,920 --> 00:38:21,258
I'M GONNA HAVE MALCOLM
DESTROY THE CAVERN.

764
00:38:21,299 --> 00:38:23,426
SACRIFICING FOUR MORE CREWMEN

765
00:38:23,468 --> 00:38:26,387
IS A SMALL PRICE TO PAY
TO SAVE<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

766
00:38:26,429 --> 00:38:28,932
TUCKER: I UNDERSTAND.

767
00:38:28,974 --> 00:38:32,185
ARCHER: NOW, I'M GONNA ASK HOSHI

768
00:38:32,227 --> 00:38:36,648
TO TELL T'POL EVERYTHING
I JUST TOLD YOU IN VULCAN.

769
00:38:36,689 --> 00:38:39,901
YOU GOT A PROBLEM WITH THAT?

770
00:38:39,943 --> 00:38:41,278
TUCKER: GO AHEAD.

771
00:38:41,319 --> 00:38:44,281
ARCHER: ENSIGN.

772
00:38:44,322 --> 00:38:46,616
[ CONVERSATION IN VULCAN ]

773
00:38:59,712 --> 00:39:01,214
[ BEEP ]

774
00:39:01,256 --> 00:39:04,676
SHE SAYS PLAYACTING ISN'T
EXACTLY A VULCAN TRADITION,

775
00:39:04,717 --> 00:39:06,928
BUT SHE'LL DO HER BEST.

776
00:39:09,722 --> 00:39:11,683
T'POL: [ SPEAKING VULCAN ]

777
00:39:34,289 --> 00:39:37,750
ARCHER: HOPE SHE
KNOWS THE DIFFERENCE
BETWEEN STUN AND KILL.

778
00:39:39,252 --> 00:39:40,670
[ BEEP ]

779
00:39:43,131 --> 00:39:47,052
THEY'VE AGREED
TO TALK TO HER, TRIP.

780
00:39:47,093 --> 00:39:48,553
SO LOWER YOUR WEAPON

781
00:39:48,594 --> 00:39:51,139
AND ACT REAL FRIENDLY.

782
00:39:58,771 --> 00:40:00,565
UGH!

783
00:40:28,968 --> 00:40:30,887
MAYWEATHER: NO.

784
00:40:31,930 --> 00:40:33,390
[ GROANS ]

785
00:41:16,975 --> 00:41:19,560
TUCKER: YOU DIDN'T SHOOT ME
LAST NIGHT, DID YOU?

786
00:41:19,602 --> 00:41:21,479
T'POL: I'M AFRAID I DID.

787
00:41:21,520 --> 00:41:25,775
MAYWEATHER: I WAS HOPING IT WAS
ALL JUST A BAD DREAM.

788
00:41:25,817 --> 00:41:28,611
TUCKER: ARE THEY GONE?

789
00:41:28,653 --> 00:41:31,614
T'POL: THEY WERE NEVER HERE.

790
00:41:31,656 --> 00:41:32,740
CUTLER: WHAT?

791
00:41:32,782 --> 00:41:34,451
T'POL: THERE WERE
NO ROCK PEOPLE.

792
00:41:34,492 --> 00:41:36,535
YOU WERE ALL HALLUCINATING.

793
00:41:36,577 --> 00:41:39,331
TUCKER: THE POLLEN?

794
00:41:39,372 --> 00:41:40,915
T'POL: YES.

795
00:41:40,957 --> 00:41:44,252
TUCKER: THEN WHAT ABOUT THAT
SPEECH YOU GAVE TO THE WALL?

796
00:41:44,294 --> 00:41:46,587
T'POL: THE CAPTAIN FELT
THAT IF I PLAYED ALONG,

797
00:41:46,629 --> 00:41:49,882
IT MIGHT HELP PERSUADE YOU
TO LOWER YOUR WEAPON.

798
00:41:49,924 --> 00:41:53,719
YOU'D GROWN INCREASINGLY
ILLOGICAL AND VIOLENT --

799
00:41:53,761 --> 00:41:57,640
SOMETHING ABOUT
SPLITTING ME IN TWO.

800
00:41:59,225 --> 00:42:03,438
TUCKER:
A PRETTY GOOD PERFORMANCE.

801
00:42:03,480 --> 00:42:08,360
LOOK, I KNOW I KIND OF SHOT
MY MOUTH OFF LAST NIGHT.

802
00:42:08,401 --> 00:42:10,320
T'POL: YOU WERE UNDER
THE INFLUENCE OF THE POLLEN.

803
00:42:10,362 --> 00:42:12,238
WE ALL WERE.

804
00:42:12,280 --> 00:42:14,491
TUCKER: CHALLENGE
YOUR PRECONCEPTIONS,

805
00:42:14,532 --> 00:42:17,369
OR THEY'LL CHALLENGE YOU.

806
00:42:17,410 --> 00:42:19,954
T'POL: COMMANDER?

807
00:42:19,996 --> 00:42:23,124
TUCKER: THAT'S SOMETHING
MR. VELIK USED TO SAY --

808
00:42:23,166 --> 00:42:26,252
10TH-GRADE BIOLOGY CLASS.

809
00:42:26,294 --> 00:42:28,421
HE WAS A VULCAN SCIENTIST

810
00:42:28,463 --> 00:42:31,257
WHO CAME TO TEACH US
ABOUT LIFE ON OTHER WORLDS.

811
00:42:31,299 --> 00:42:34,469
I'D NEVER SEEN A VULCAN BEFORE.

812
00:42:34,511 --> 00:42:35,928
NOT UP CLOSE.

813
00:42:35,970 --> 00:42:40,183
[ CHUCKLES ]
HE SCARED THE HELL OUT OF ME.

814
00:42:40,225 --> 00:42:44,103
T'POL: PERHAPS IT'S NOT TOO LATE
TO FOLLOW HIS ADVICE.

815
00:42:46,231 --> 00:42:51,194
MAYWEATHER: OW. I MUST'VE
TWISTED UP MY NECK.

816
00:42:51,236 --> 00:42:53,612
HOW'S NOVAKOVICH?

817
00:42:53,654 --> 00:42:55,114
DO WE KNOW?

818
00:42:55,156 --> 00:42:57,909
T'POL: THE CAPTAIN SAYS
HE'S GOING TO BE FINE.

819
00:42:57,950 --> 00:43:00,328
[ SHUTTLEPOD APPROACHING ]

820
00:43:12,924 --> 00:43:15,134
CUTLER: OH...
